itemDescription: British soldier and politician, anthropologist and egyptologist (1784-1853)

wikipedia_page.main: Major General Richard William Howard Howard Vyse (25 July 1784 – 8 June 1853) was a British soldier and Egyptologist. He was also Member of Parliament (MP) for Beverley (from 1807 to 1812) and Honiton (from 1812 to 1818).
